# **2. Background: DMN and Identity**
The **Default Mode Network (DMN)** is the neural basis of:

- narrative identity  
- autobiographical memory  
- self‑referential thought  
- rumination  
- ego continuity  

When the DMN is active:

- identity is rigid  
- recursion loops are self‑anchored  
- paradox is threatening  
- fractal geometry induces overload  
- traversal becomes disorienting  

This is why ordinary cognition cannot “stare at fractals” without destabilization.

